---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Telemetry — Verfix"
  description="What Verfix collects, why, and how to opt out. Anonymous usage data only. No personal information."
>
  <main class="tl-page">
    <div class="tl-inner">
      <h1 class="tl-title">Telemetry</h1>
      <p class="tl-subtitle">What Verfix collects, why, and how to opt out.</p>

      <div class="tl-notice">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Telemetry is not yet implemented in the current release.
        This page documents what will be collected when it ships. No data is currently sent.
      </div>

      <p class="tl-body">
        The Verfix CLI will collect anonymous usage data to understand how developers use
        the tool. This helps prioritize what to fix and build next. No personal information
        is ever collected.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tl-h2">What we will collect</h2>

      <table class="tl-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Field</th>
            <th>Example</th>
            <th>Why</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>command</td><td>"run"</td><td>Know which commands are used most</td></tr>
          <tr><td>passed</td><td>true / false</td><td>Understand overall pass rates</td></tr>
          <tr><td>failure_type</td><td>"selector_not_found"</td><td>Know what breaks most often</td></tr>
          <tr><td>cli_version</td><td>"0.1.4"</td><td>Track adoption of versions</td></tr>
          <tr><td>platform</td><td>"linux"</td><td>Know which OS to prioritize</td></tr>
          <tr><td>node_version</td><td>"v20.11.0"</td><td>Compatibility decisions</td></tr>
          <tr><td>anonymous_id</td><td>UUID (random)</td><td>Count unique users without identifying them</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="tl-h2">What we will never collect</h2>

      <ul class="tl-never">
        <li>IP addresses</li>
        <li>Project names or file paths</li>
        <li>Selectors, URLs, or any app-specific data</li>
        <li>Personal information of any kind</li>
        <li>Environment variables or secrets</li>
        <li>Source code or file contents</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="tl-h2">How to opt out</h2>

      <p class="tl-body">When telemetry ships, you will be able to opt out at any time:</p>

      <div class="tl-code">verfix telemetry disable</div>

      <p class="tl-body">Or set an environment variable:</p>

      <div class="tl-code"># In your shell profile or .env<br />export VERFIX_TELEMETRY=0</div>

      <h2 class="tl-h2">CI environments</h2>

      <p class="tl-body">
        Telemetry will be automatically disabled in CI environments when the
        <code class="tl-inline">CI=true</code> environment variable is set
        (standard on GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, CircleCI, etc.).
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .tl-page {
    padding-top: 56px; /* offset fixed nav */
  }
  .tl-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
  }
  .tl-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .tl-subtitle {
    color: var(--vf-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .tl-notice {
    background: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--vf-amber);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .tl-h2 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .tl-body {
    color: var(--vf-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .tl-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    background: var(--vf-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--vf-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .tl-table th {
    background: var(--vf-surface-2);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--vf-text-secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--vf-border);
  }
  .tl-table td {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--vf-border-subtle);
    color: var(--vf-text);
  }
  .tl-table td:first-child {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--vf-green);
  }
  .tl-table td:nth-child(2) {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--vf-amber);
  }
  .tl-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .tl-never {
    background: var(--vf-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--vf-border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--vf-green);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem 1.25rem 2rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .tl-never li {
    color: var(--vf-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .tl-code {
    background: var(--vf-terminal-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--vf-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--vf-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .tl-inline {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--vf-amber);
    background: rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.08);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
</style>
